The Edo State Governor, Godwin Obaseki has been sworn-in for a second term in office. Obaseki was sworn-in at the Samuel Ogbemudia Stadium in Benin, the state capital, on Thursday. The incumbent governor had defeated his closest rival, Pastor Osagie Ize-Iyamu during the last governorship election in the state. Obaseki, who was the governorship candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party, PDP, had defeated Ize-Iyamu of the All Progressives Congress, PAC.